title: HXR Phase shifter 46 has an error, this prevents the HXR taper from loading automatically. Notified Alex
text: I received a CATER for energy change refusing to load the HXR Taper which led me to this. For context: Heinz-Dieter, Alex and I agreed recently that if there is an issue with any undulator or phase shifter in the line, that the GUI (and similarly SCORE) should not load any of the undulators and should instead complain to the user. Energy change notifies the user and tells them the specific problem in the GUI message window and also the xterm. The response should be to contact Alex or Heinz-Dieter to fix the problem with whatever undulator or phase shifter is showing a fault. The taper load failed at 15:03 today because phase shifter 46 has an encoder fault. I've forwarded the CATER to Alex and also emailed her a message to please look at the phase shifter. Once the fault is cleared, the GUI and SCORE should work just fine for loading the undulator taper.

title: HXR Phase shifter 46 has an error, this prevents the HXR taper from loading automatically. Notified A. Montironi
text: I received a CATER for energy change refusing to load the HXR Taper which led me to this. For context: Heinz-Dieter, Alex and I agreed recently that if there is an issue with any undulator or phase shifter in the line, that the GUI (and similarly SCORE) should not load any of the undulators and should instead complain to the user. Energy change notifies the user and tells them the specific problem in the GUI message window and also the xterm. The response should be to contact Alex or Heinz-Dieter to fix the problem with whatever undulator or phase shifter is showing a fault. The taper load failed at 15:03 today because phase shifter 46 has an encoder fault that appears sometimes. This was captured in cater 154751, and likely won't be fixed until a PAMM, but does not physically prevent the phase shifter from operating. Alex will ask Heinz-Dieter if we can disable the encoder fault reporting. For now though, SCORE and Energy Change will refuse to load the HXR Taper.

title: Shift summary: Wednesday swing
text: SUMMARY: User beam for 7 hours of this 8-hour shift. Lost beam once, then had an MCOR fault, then lost beam during injection. All appears to be OK now. Average fill rate was around 42mA/minute, average calculated efficiency was around 95%. INJECTOR: 250-300mV Q. Tuned once between fills to improve Q meter and fill rate. SPEAR: Lost beam at 10:23pm. Symptoms appeared to be a power dip. After the beam loss 09S-COR3H was unresponsive (readback always zero). A power tech was still on site, so he came down and replaced it very quickly. During the refill, beam was lost with about 200mA stored when the RF 12kV contactor opened. There was no MPS fault or clear indication why. Everything reset OK, and 500mA was redelivered at 11:23pm.

title: OFF NORMAL: ACR reports LOA switch tripped
text: ACR states that they were in the process of recovering beam when it happened. ICS2 supply flow to LOA, LOB and TCAV circuits in the Vault was adjusting to to the change in temperature. At one point the flow was decreasing and the flow to LOA was lowered enough to trip the switch. Once ICS2 flow went up in adjusting to temperature, the flows to the vault increased and LOA reset. Might be worth going in next PAMM and checking the settings - either the switch calibration drifted off a bit high or the trip point may need to be adjusted to compensate for the oscillations in the flow as the temperature comes into range.
